HEADWORD: Honeyberry
<hw>Hon"ey*ber`ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu>pl.
<plw>-berries</plw>.</plu> <def>The fruit of either of two trees having
sweetish berries: <it>(a)</it> An Old World hackberry (<spn>Celtis
australis</spn>). <it>(b)</it> In the West Indies, the genip
(<spn>Melicocca bijuga</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
